CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1955, pg. 25, reads: "The Rented House - The Sanfords rented the above house from Coraopolis Real Estate Dealer A. D. Rossi, but because of threats and acts of bigots cancelled their lease Friday afternoon. 'We would have stayed, but my wife has a nervous condition.' Mahlon Sanford, the husband, said. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two story light colored frame house, street no. 226, with porch rail with diamond shape, and overgrown lot on right, Coraopolis
